&lt;li&gt;Create and manage Onboarding permit drawings (light, permit, enterprise).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with schematic design and tender package creation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Convert point clouds into Revit models and support with sales plans.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Model Revit families and assist in basic building systems coordination.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Produce graphic materials and presentations to communicate design concepts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide testfit design support as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we’re looking for&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Education: Bachelor’s in Architecture, Civil Engineering, or related field (Professional degree preferred).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience with Revit (modeling, families, point cloud conversion).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in AutoCAD and SketchUp.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in BIM workflows, particularly in architecture or engineering projects.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of building information modeling standards and best practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with construction documentation and design coordination.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
