&lt;li&gt;Operate at the critical junction between strategy and results: our team exists because great ideas, technical developments, and great products and tools die without someone owning the last mile. You&#39;ll make sure they don&#39;t.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate across every level and format: present to 3-5 regional leaders in a working session, run a 100+ person enablement rollout the next day, write the memo that gets leadership to act. The audience changes constantly -- you adapt and move like a fish in the water across all of them.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Scale what works: take proven frameworks from North America and roll them out globally, adapting for regional context without letting each market start from scratch. Just as importantly, identify what&#39;s working in other regions that could be scaled back to North America.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build whatever the project needs to succeed: presentations, playbooks, dashboards, trainings, SOPs, tools, etc. When the unlock is a piece of tooling or automation, you build it. When it&#39;s a deck that rewires how a team thinks, you build that too.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive urgency relentlessly: we sit at the end of the funnel where business results are made or missed, and every week of slow adoption costs real revenue. You push stakeholders to move fast and hold them accountable.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pursue excellence in everything you produce -- every analysis, every deck, every dashboard, every training -- with the energy and attitude to sustain high speed, high pressure, and high autonomy over time.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
